{"type":"message","id":"37fb84fc","parentId":"684976f3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:03:43.788Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c73hybnip16b_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 130314\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI compression experiment is done, revealing the \"constant format problem\"\r\n- Key insight: Three-dimensional filter needed: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n- Next experiment pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (Strategy C)\r\n- Need to distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action based on the insights would be:\r\n1. Implement the hybrid scoring experiment (pending)\r\n2. Update the compression synthesis document with the three-dimensional filter\r\n3. Create an implementation of the new scoring formula\r\n\r\nGiven the insights, the most actionable next step is to actually implement the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring function and test it against the prior results. This is the \"next experiment\" mentioned in the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist that I could modify:\r\n- research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md - the synthesis document\r\n- pulse.ps1 - the pulse script\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to implement the scoring function in a testable way. I could update the synthesis document with the concrete formula, or I could create a simple test script.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the insights:\r\n- **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis formula could be implemented and tested. But I need to think about what single action advances the goals most.\r\n\r\nThe pending items are:\r\n1. Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n2. Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n3. Implement CFI filtering\r\n4. Wire to TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design compression network\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step based on the CFI experiment findings would be to:\r\n\r\n\r\n1. Create a test script implementing the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Update the synthesis with the concrete scoring function\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a precise implementation of the scoring mechanism. The formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) provides a clear mathematical framework for evaluating token significance. By creating a test script, I can validate the approach and generate empirical data to support the next experimental phase.\r\n\r\nThe key is to translate the theoretical insights into a tangible, testable implementation that can reveal nuanced differences in token processing. This approach bridges the gap between conceptual understanding and practical application.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment revealed that the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) is the correct approach, but the scoring formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) hasn't been tested yet against the actual pulse data.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a scoring implementation script that tests the hybrid formula against the existing pulse corpus, generating comparative metrics to validate whether this approach better distinguishes \"constant format\" (high freq, high CFI) from \"research trajectory\" (moderate freq, moderate CFI).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\n# New file: research/cfi_hybrid_scorer.py\r\n\"\"\"\r\nHybrid CFI×Freq scoring for compression filtering.\r\nFormula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nGoal: Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\nExpected: constant-format tokens get capped at ~1.0×1.0=1.0, research tokens get 0.5-0.95×0.5-1.0\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport json\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data (assumes token_analysis.json exists from prior analysis)\r\nTOKEN_ANALYSIS = Path(\"research/token_analysis.json\")\r\nPULSES_DIR = Path(\"pulses\")\r\nOUTPUT = Path(\"research/hybrid_scoring_results.json\")\r\n\r\ndef compute_hybrid_score(cfi: float, freq: int, freq_cap: int = 120) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"CFI × min(1, freq/freq_cap)\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / freq_cap)\r\n\r\ndef load_token_analysis() -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Load existing token analysis data.\"\"\"\r\n    if TOKEN_ANALYSIS.exists():\r\n        with open(TOKEN_ANALYSIS, 'r') as f:\r\n            return json.load(f)\r\n    return {}\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    tokens = load_token_analysis()\r\n    \r\n    results = {\r\n        \"formula\": \"score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\",\r\n        \"freq_cap\": 120,\r\n        \"tokens\": {},\r\n        \"summary\": {\r\n            \"constant_format_candidates\": [],  # High freq, high CFI\r\n            \"research_trajectory_candidates\": [],  # Moderate freq, moderate-high CFI\r\n            \"poor_signals\": []  # Low CFI or very low freq\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    for token, data in tokens.items():\r\n        cfi = data.get(\"cfi\", 0.0)\r\n        freq = data.get(\"freq\", 0)\r\n        score = compute_hybrid_score(cfi, freq)\r\n        \r\n        results[\"tokens\"][token] = {\r\n            \"cfi\": cfi,\r\n            \"freq\": freq,\r\n            \"hybrid_score\": round(score, 4),\r\n            \"classification\": None\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        # Classification logic\r\n        if freq >= 140 and cfi >= 0.95:\r\n            results[\"summary\"][\"constant_format_candidates\"].append(token)\r\n            results[\"tokens\"][token][\"classification\"] = \"constant_format\"\r\n        elif \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:03:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371823787}}
