{"type":"message","id":"974c66ea","parentId":"53430aec","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:03:53.828Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the mutation from 13:02:16 was moved to the rejected folder. The proposed folder is empty. The new pulse created a new session log but the mutation was cut off/incomplete. Let me look at the most recent rejected mutation to understand why it was rejected.","thinkingSignature":"8f5ac8841650201c62dc8fa6f8062310ca74f9f1f1f33e8c695ec2e083d46141"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_blur4aqq65mm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\rejected\\2026-03-24 130216.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2451,"output":110,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14698,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774371831118}}
{"type":"message","id":"9cab6d7e","parentId":"974c66ea","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:03:53.833Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_blur4aqq65mm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿Python\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n\"\"\"\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\n================================================\nTest the hybrid scoring formula against binary threshold strategies.\n\nFormula: score(T) = CFI(T) * min(1, freq(T)/120)\nHypothesis: Filters out constant-format tokens while preserving research trajectory tokens.\n\nCompare with Strategy A (freq-only, threshold=60) and Strategy B (CFI≥0.7 AND freq<60).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef load_pulses(pulses_dir=\"pulses\"):\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse files and extract tokens.\"\"\"\n    pulses_path = Path(pulses_dir)\n    if not pulses_path.exists():\n        print(f\"Error: {pulses_dir} not found\")\n        return None, None\n    \n    # Load ground truth (manual selections from research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md)\n    # Format: {pulse_id: [token1, token2, ...]}\n    ground_truth = {\n        \"pulse_2026-03-22_001503\": [\"Phase 1\", \"architecture\", \"Compositional Cognition\", \n                                    \"TemporalAttention\", \"Infant\", \"synthesis\", \"compatible\"],\n        \"pulse_2026-03-22_001815\": [\"gap-decay\", \"λ\", \"decay rate\", \"session gaps\", \n                                    \"compression\", \"temporal hashing\"],\n        \"pulse_2026-03-24_125915\": [\"CFI\", \"compression\", \"constant format\", \"precision\",\n                                    \"recall\", \"freq\", \"threshold\", \"strategy\"],\n    }\n    \n    tokens_by_pulse = {}\n    for pulse_file in sorted(pulses_path.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\n        with open(pulse_file, 'r') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n        tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]{2,}\\b', content.lower()))\n        tokens_by_pulse[pulse_file.stem] = tokens\n    \n    return tokens_by_pulse, ground_truth\n\ndef calculate_hybrid_scores(token_stats):\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculate hybrid CFI×Freq scores.\n    score(T) = CFI(T) * min(1, freq(T)/120)\n    \"\"\"\n    scores = {}\n    for token, (freq, cfi) in token_stats.items():\n        freq_component = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n        score = cfi * freq_component\n        scores[token] = score\n    return scores\n\ndef run_experiment():\n    \"\"\"Run Strategy C hybrid scoring experiment.\"\"\"\n    tokens_by_p\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371833832}}
{"type":"message","id":"426af304","parentId":"9cab6d7e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:04:03.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mutation was cut off mid-file and was rejected because of the incomplete content. The sandbox ran, saw the mutation was incomplete, and rejected it. \n\nNow let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle:\n\n1. The CFI compression experiment from the last pulse revealed that the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) is correct, but the scoring formula hasn't been tested yet\n2. This pulse attempted to create a scoring implementation script to test the hybrid CFI×Freq formula\n3. The mutation was cut off (hit token limit during parsing) and was rejected\n4. A new session log was created\n\nSo the key outcome: Pulse completed, one mutation was rejected (incomplete), no mutations were applied. \n\nThe sandbox is still working through the CFI compression formula and hasn't resolved the scoring implementation yet. I should document this for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"d8a6d23cbfbcded8a735bbefe0b5d12f90d8a8b36d0589072f82cba1a7e43fbf"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-24 13:03:14 Summary**\n\n**What happened:**\n- The previous pulse's CFI experiment revealed that the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) is correct, but the hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` hasn't been validated against actual pulse data yet.\n- This pulse attempted to create `research/cfi_hybrid_scorer.py` to test that formula.\n- **Mutation was rejected** — the file content was truncated mid-write (hit the token limit during parsing), so it was moved to `mutations/rejected/` rather than applied.\n- 5 files changed overall (commits on master `bcadf70`), mostly housekeeping.\n\n**Current state:** No mutations applied this cycle. The hybrid scoring experiment is still pending — needs a complete implementation script to test the formula against the pulse corpus.\n\n**Outstanding question from the experiment:** How to distinguish \"constant format\" tokens (freq ≈ 160, CFI = 1.0) from \"research trajectory\" tokens (moderate freq, moderate-high CFI) using the hybrid formula. The capping behavior at freq ≥ 120 needs validation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3137,"output":451,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774371833834}}
